#Text=Washington Dulles International Airport
#Text=Washington Dulles International Airport ( IAD ) is the main international airport of the Washington , D.C. area and surrounding communities .
#Text=Understand
#Text=Dulles is 26 miles west of DC in Sterling , Virginia .
#Text=It is the primary international and long-haul gateway to the region .
#Text=Opened in 1962 to relieve Washington National Airport ( now Reagan National ) , it soon became an enduring mark in the nation 's architecture .
#Text=The main terminal , designed by Eero Saarinen , is an architectural masterpiece , with a curved roof that arcs gracefully into air , suspended over a huge open ticketing and check-in area .

#Text=At one point , this was the only building at the airport , and instead of the usual affair of the time where passengers walked to their plane on the tarmac , special shuttles known as " mobile lounges " and " plane mates " were used to ferry passengers between the terminal and their planes .

column1: #Text=Unfortunately the layout has n't responded well to the changed needs of modern air travel .
#Text=In order to accommodate larger jets and more aerobridges , two satellite buildings were built over time .

#Text=The layout includes lengthy corridors and long escalators and you will have to take a train between the main building and the concourses - expect that you will need some extra time to get to the gate .
#Text=Many carriers serve the airport , which serves as an East Coast hub for United Airlines and a major gateway for Star Alliance airlines .

#Text=Now , the main terminal primarily houses ticket counters , baggage claim , and security screening , with only a handful of passenger gates , while the vast majority of flights arrive and depart from the two midfield terminals accessed by train , walkway , or mobile lounge .
#Text=Detailed map of terminal and concourses
#Text=Interactive map
#Text=Security
#Text=There are two entrances to the screening area , the West and East Security Checkpoints .
#Text=TSA PreCheck and the private service CLEAR have set up their checkpoints for departing passengers in between the two general checkpoints .
#Text=Flights
#Text=Concourse A
#Text=United Express
#Text=International Departures : Air China , Copa , Ethiopian
#Text=Concourse B
#Text=International Departures : Air India , ANA , Austrian , Avianca , Brussels Airlines , Lufthansa , SAS , South African , Turkish Airlines
#Text=Aer Lingus ( all flights , due to preclearance )
#Text=Concourse C
#Text=United and United Express only , as well as processing for international Star Alliance arrivals
#Text=Concourse D
#Text=United and United Express only
#Text=Concourse H
#Text=Waiting area for airlines with only plane mates
#Text=Concourse Z
#Text=Air Canada ( all flights due to preclearance ) , Frontier
#Text=International Arrivals Building ( IAB )
#Text=Gate for almost all international flights arriving at Dulles , with the exception of pre-clearance flights and Star Alliance flights .
#Text=This building uses plane mates to take passengers from the plane to the building fr processing .
#Text=Departure
#Text=Each airline has a specific location for their check-in counters :
#Text=Ticket Counter 1
#Text=Aer Lingus , Aeroflot , Aeromexico , Air China , Air India , British Airways , Delta , Ethiopian , Etihad , Primera , Porter , Southwest , Volaris
#Text=Ticket Counter 2
#Text=Air France , American , Brussels , Copa , Emirates , KLM , Korean Air , Qatar , Royal Air Maroc , Saudia , Virgin Atlantic
#Text=Ticket Counter 3
#Text=Air Canada , Alaska , ANA , Austrian , Avancia , Frontier , Icelandair , jetBlue , Lufthansa , SAS , South African , Turkish
#Text=Ticket Counter 4
#Text=United and United Express
#Text=only
#Text=The ticket counter numbers are designated by the order you pass them as you drive into the airport complex .
#Text=For example , Counter 2 would be the second counter complex passed .
#Text=This also means that the counter numbers are ordered in a west to east fashion ( ex . 1 is the westernmost counter and 4 is the easternmost ) .
#Text=Entering the airport means that you are facing a southerly direction , so keep that in mind when looking for your counter .
#Text=The airport has drop off zones at each counter , so you can stop at the zone corresponding to the number of your counter .
#Text=Arrival
#Text=Some airlines have specific baggage claims for arriving passengers :
#Text=Claims 1-5 - United
#Text=Claims
#Text=6
#Text=- United , Aer Lingus
#Text=Claim 7 - Frontier
#Text=Claim 8 - special claim for oversized baggage
#Text=Claim 10 - jetBlue
#Text=Claims 11-12 - American , Ethiad
#Text=Claims 13-14 - Delta , Southwest
#Text=Claim 15 - All international arrivals except for preclearance flights
#Text=There is no Claim
#Text=9 .
#Text=Customs
#Text=Star Alliance international arrivals
#Text=arrive at the C concourse , where you go via a secure hallway between the sterile area and the windows on the edge of the concourse to the east end .
#Text=There , you go through customs .
#Text=At Dulles , if you get an orange box at passport control , you must go to a secondary screening room with your bags .
#Text=Otherwise , you can simply take your checked bags off the conveyor and recheck them after walking about 50 feet ( dogs will sniff your bag along the way ) .
#Text=Afterwards , you reclear security .
#Text=There are separate lines for U.S./Canadian and foreign nationals , the former getting TSA Precheck automatically and thus will not have to remove their belts and shoes .
#Text=Public transit
#Text=The Silver Line Express Bus operates every 15 minutes between the airport and the garage near the Wiehle-Reston East Metrorail Station ( Silver Line ) .
#Text=The bus journey takes 10 minutes and costs $ 5 .
#Text=From there , after crossing the pedestrian bridge over the highway to reach the Metrorail station , the journey by Metrorail to the East End takes another 45 minutes .

#Text=A cheaper but slower option to get from the airport to the garage near the Metrorail station is to take Fairfax Connector Bus Routes 981/983 which depart the airport every 20 minutes from 9AM-7PM and every 40 minutes from 6AM-9AM and 7PM-11PM .
#Text=The bus journey takes 30 minutes and costs $ 2.00 .
#Text=The Silver Line of the Metrorail is being extended to the airport ; however , the projected completion date is in 2021 .

#Text=Metrobus 5A makes stops in Herndon , Tysons Corner , Rosslyn Metrorail Station ( Blue/Orange/Silver Lines ) , and L'Enfant Plaza Metrorail Station ( Green/Yellow/Blue/Orange/Silver Lines ) , a few blocks south of the National Mall .

#Text=It generally departs from the airport every 40 minutes on weekdays and hourly ( though not on the hour ) on weekends , taking 40-50 minutes to the Rosslyn Metrorail Station and 50-60 minutes to the L'Enfant Plaza Metrorail Station .
#Text=The fare is $ 7.50 one-way ( no change given ) .
#Text=The bus stops near Curb 2E outside of the airport terminal .
#Text=Fairfax Connector Bus #983 to the Smithsonian National Air and Space Museum 's Udvar-Hazy Center .
#Text=The bus departs from the airport every 20 minutes daily , costing $ 2.00 and taking 12 minutes to reach the museum .
